          <updateDate>2015-06-01T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Sanchez-Young Social Security Disability Insurance for the Terminally Ill Act </b></p> <p> This bill amends title II (Old Age, Survivors and Disability Insurance) of the Social Security Act to eliminate the waiting period for disability insurance benefits for terminally ill individuals with a life expectancy of 12 months or less, as determined by a primary care provider, medical specialist, or other qualified provider, or who would otherwise suffer undue hardship by application of a waiting period.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-06-24T19:58:16Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        </item>
